						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab built into the left outer wall of the Chanḍēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Trailōkyamalla (Sōmēśvara I)—A.D. 1056-57.</p>						

						<p>The available details of date of this damaged record are <hi rend="bold">Śaka 97[8], Durmukhi-Bhādrapada, Sunday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1056-57.</hi></p>						

						<p>It refers to a certain Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara (name lost) and seems to record a gift of land, etc., by certain individuals. The record is badly worn out and the details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
